# log-lens Project Rules

## Project Purpose
AI-powered log file analyser. Rust for parsing/aggregation/serving.
Anthropic API for analysis. Web UI for charts and interactive Q&A.

## Non-Negotiable Architecture Rules

### The AnalysisEngine Trait
The AI layer MUST be accessed only through the `AnalysisEngine` trait defined in `src/ai/mod.rs`.
Never reference `AnthropicEngine` directly outside of `src/ai/`.
This boundary exists so the AI layer can be replaced with a Python microservice without
touching any other code.

```rust
// CORRECT — depend on the trait
async fn handle_analysis(engine: &dyn AnalysisEngine, summary: &LogSummary) { ... }

// WRONG — never do this outside src/ai/
let engine = AnthropicEngine::new(api_key);
```

### Log Summary — Never Raw Lines
The LLM receives a `LogSummary` struct (aggregated stats), never raw log content.
This keeps token usage low and is a deliberate design decision. Do not change this.

### Typed Domain Model
All parsed log lines become `LogRecord` enum variants. No HashMaps, no String fields
where structured types are possible.

### Error Handling
Use `anyhow::Result` throughout library code. No `.unwrap()` or `.expect()` except
in tests or truly unrecoverable startup situations.

### Async Runtime
Tokio only. Do not introduce a second async runtime.

### API Key
Always read from `std::env::var("ANTHROPIC_API_KEY")`. Never hardcode.

## Parser Architecture
Parsers implement the `Parser` trait from `src/parser/mod.rs`.
Format detection is automatic from file content sampling.
AI-inferred parsing (`src/parser/ai_infer.rs`) is the fallback only — check built-ins first.
Inferred schemas are cached to avoid repeated API calls.

## Current Model
Use `claude-sonnet-4-20250514` for all Anthropic API calls.
Max tokens: 1024 for analysis, 512 for chat responses.
Always include the aggregated summary as context in chat turns.

## File Ownership
- `src/parser/` — parsing only, no AI calls except ai_infer.rs
- `src/aggregator.rs` — pure computation, no I/O
- `src/summary.rs` — serialisation only
- `src/ai/` — all LLM interaction
- `src/server.rs` — HTTP only, delegates to ai/ and aggregator
- `frontend/index.html` — single file, no build step required

## Samples
`samples/` contains synthetic log data only. Never commit real log files.
